# Frontend Angular — Conventions

## Architecture

- Angular 19 with standalone components (NO NgModules)
- Features lazy-loaded by route
- Singleton services in `core/`
- Shared components in `shared/`
- Signals for reactive state

## Frontend stack

- PwC AppKit 4 (`@appkit4/angular-components`) as the UI component library
- Tailwind CSS 4 for styling
- Cytoscape.js for graph visualization
- SSE (Server-Sent Events) for agent chat streaming

## UI library — AppKit 4

- Component, design-token, icon, and pattern reference lives in [`docs/appkit4/`](../../docs/appkit4/).
- **Before writing UI**, consult `docs/appkit4/AGENTS.md` (rules for AI) and `docs/appkit4/components/INDEX.md`; use design tokens (`docs/appkit4/design-tokens/`) instead of hard-coded hex/px.
- Use AppKit layout/shell components and `ap-panel`; don't invent custom app chrome.

## Language rule (strict)

- **Everything in English**: code (variables, methods, classes, components, services), file names, routes, comments, technical documentation.
- **Spanish only for**: end-user facing content (UI labels, error messages, tooltips, placeholder text, user-visible strings).
- Example: component is `LegalNormListComponent`, route is `/legal-norms`, but the template shows "Normas Legales".

## Reminder

- Do not create code directly unless the user requests it
